## Summary

**Code changes:**
- Created `src/engine/claude/sandbox.policy.ts` with `buildSandboxPolicy()` that maps `--sandbox` flag values to fascicle's `SandboxProviderConfig`. Two frozen allowlist consts deep-equal the Phase 0 baselines. Legacy `greywallProvider` and `isAvailable` co-located here with a Phase-7 deferral comment so `claude.exec.ts` keeps working.
- Reduced `src/engine/claude/sandbox.ts` — removed `node:child_process` import; imports `greywallProvider` and `isAvailable` from `sandbox.policy`.
- Deleted `src/engine/claude/sandbox.greywall.ts`.
- Added `rules/no-child-process-in-sandbox.yml` (severity: error) enforcing the boundary.

**Tests:**
- New `src/engine/claude/__tests__/sandbox.policy.test.ts` — 19 unit tests covering allowlist baseline equality, return shape per flag value, `additional_write_paths` semantics, override fields.
- New `src/engine/__tests__/sandbox.parity.test.ts` — 6 sandbox-parity regression tests (network + filesystem enforcement parity between new policy and legacy spawn wrapper).
- Minimal updates to existing tests: `sandbox.greywall.test.ts` (1-line import path) and `sandbox.test.ts` (3-line partial-mock pattern via `vi.importActual`). Every test name and assertion body unchanged. **38 sandbox tests pass; 1178 total unit tests pass.**

**Check status:** 7 of 8 green (types, lint, struct, dead, docs, spell, test). The `agents` (agnix) check fails for environmental reasons — agnix's postinstall fetches a platform binary from `github.com/agent-sh/agnix/releases/...` which the active sandbox blocks (`Proxy CONNECT aborted due to timeout` at greyproxy; `cargo install agnix-cli` fallback also times out at `index.crates.io`). This is the same shape as Phase 0's `mutation-score.json` (`captured: false`) deferral. The harness must re-run `npm run check` from a context with the binary pre-staged. Documented comprehensively in `handoff-02-sandbox-policy.md`.

`phase-2-check.json` captured. `ridgeline build` is operational.

