[review:09-build-auto-sigint-dogfood] AC1-5,7-10,12-13 verified. AC6 test fixture doesn't run a `ridgeline build`. AC11 parenthetical violated by lingering pipeline imports.
[ridgeline] [09-build-auto-sigint-dogfood] FAILED: Phase migrates build/auto onto fascicle flows, captures dogfood evidence, and ships `npm run check` green. AC1–5, AC7–10, AC12–13 pass cleanly. Two ACs fail: AC6's SIGINT regression test spawns a minimal fascicle fixture instead of a `ridgeline build` child process — sub-criteria (b)/(c)/(d) are not actually verified — and AC11's parenthetical ("no command path imports it") is violated: src/commands/build.ts still imports `runPhase`, `buildPhaseGraph`, `validateGraph`, `getReadyPhases`, `hasParallelism`, and four worktree helpers from src/engine/pipeline/. Both deviations are explicitly acknowledged in the handoff but block the phase as written.
