The critical failure: this phase's entire purpose is to capture the Stryker mutation scores BEFORE Phase 11 deletes `src/engine/pipeline/`. The Phase 10 spec is explicit: *"this phase first captures the absolute pre-migration score on `src/engine/pipeline/` — which still exists at this point — outside the active sandbox, writes it into the baseline file, and only then asserts the new-scope score is ≥ that captured number. Running mutation testing AFTER pipeline deletion would make the baseline capture impossible."* The Required Tools section mandates running with `RIDGELINE_SANDBOX=0` OR `pool: 'forks'`. Both were attempted; both failed. No mutation score was captured. The gate script returns DEFERRED (exit 0) when scores are missing, which means it can never fail and is not a real assertion. Per reviewer rules, a tool failure where the foundation does not actually work is an automatic phase-fail.
